ens\nscripts/ralph/README.md:82:- inspect artifact files when the compact log points to a failed phase\nscripts/ralph/README.md:83:- `state/run-log.md` also appends a compact health line after each cycle: `o` for promoted success, `x` for completed non-promotion/failure or RCA auto-branch, and `!` for a stalled worker cycle\nscripts/ralph/README.md:94:### Run a longer unattended loop\nscripts/ralph/README.md:105:tail -f state/run-log.md\nscripts/ralph/README.md:109:ls logs/\nscripts/ralph/README.md:110:tail -f logs/server-*.log\nscripts/ralph/README.md:132:- `run-once.sh` always rewrites `state/current-cycle.json`, `state/evaluation.json`, `state/backlog.md`, and `state/last-result.txt`; treat those as loop-owned state.\nscripts/ralph/README.md:133:- if the worker goes silent and `worker.jsonl` stops changing past the stall timeout, the harness marks the cycle as `stalled`, writes a stall artifact, appends `!` to the health line, and stops the unattended loop for operator triage unless that identical stall has already repeated enough times to auto-branch into RCA\nscripts/ralph/README.md:140:- Port cleanup is executed automatically only by the evaluator path for `npm run verify`, `npm run test:e2e`, or other Playwright-bearing commands. Manual local runs do not get that cleanup for free.\nscripts/ralph/README.md:141:- `ensure-e2e-port-free.sh` is intentionally aggressive and may terminate unrelated processes bound to `127.0.0.1:3100`.\nscripts/ralph/README.md:142:- `state/current-task.txt` must point at a task that still exists in `docs/exec-plans/active/` with status `active` or `queued`, or be `NONE` only when the runnable queue is exhausted.\nscripts/ralph/README.md:145:- `ensure-state.mjs` repairs obvious drift before status/loop runs by rewriting `state/current-task.txt` to the current runnable task or `NONE`, and it refreshes `state/backlog.md`.\nscripts/ralph/README.md:147:- if `current-task.txt` is invalid and there is no runnable task to repair to, treat that as queue exhaustion or operator repair work; do not keep rerunning the loop expecting progress.\nAGENTS.md:6:This repository is optimized for agent-legible development and a Ralph-style task-promotion loop.\nAGENTS.md:24:- no-auth, Basic, and OAuth bearer MCP/REST runtime paths\nAGENTS.md:26:- failure simulation, audit log, server config, reset, logging, Docker/Nginx guidance, and Ralph harness\nAGENTS.md:41:- mock OAuth authorization server with login, consent, token, revocation, and discovery metadata\nAGENTS.md:46:- Prisma plus SQLite for migrations, seed defaults, and persistent runtime state\nAGENTS.md:47:- layered domain shape: types, config, repo, service, runtime, UI\nAGENTS.md:49:- logs/ plus LOG_LEVEL and start:logged for operator-visible server flow\nAGENTS.md:54:- integration tests for repository/runtime boundaries where needed\nAGENTS.md:62:For manual server inspection, prefer `npm run start:logged` and set `LOG_LEVEL` intentionally instead of relying only on ephemeral terminal output.\nARCHITECTURE.md:8:- a public Next.js UI served on port 3000\nARCHITECTURE.md:11:- operator logs under logs/ with LOG_LEVEL selection\nARCHITECTURE.md:12:- Ralph scripts under scripts/ralph/ driving active task promotion\nARCHITECTURE.md:32:| Endpoint catalog | Endpoint CRUD, parameters, response cases, delete code, enabled state |\nARCHITECTURE.md:33:| Matcher/runtime | Argument normalization, exact match, default/no-match, delay/error/malformed behavior |\nARCHITECTURE.md:39:| Operations | SQLite prep, seed defaults, base URL, Docker/Nginx docs, logs, health |\nARCHITECTURE.md:47:- OAuth login and consent UI is separate from the admin navigation\nARCHITECTURE.md:51:- domain services own validation, matching, auth, token, and reset logic\nARCHITECTURE.md:54:- startup code prepares runtime state before production-style serving\nARCHITECTURE.md:58:- Prisma migrations define the schema and db:prepare applies migrations plus idempotent seed defaults\nARCHITECTURE.md:66:- 